From Doug Zolmer Subject Re Manual Shift Bigots In article kissane John Kissane writes As a matter of interest does anyone know why autos are so popular in the US while here in Europe they are rare Just In many of our cities there are traffic signals every feet unsynchronised of course well here in Ottawa anyway and the roads are so congested that shifting manually is a real pain in the left Also most Canadians are too stupid to learn how to shift manually gee I gotta co ordinate my two feet on the clutch brake and accelerator and I gotta steer shift and operate the signals optional and radio with my two it can't be done Also most North American made cars come with the automatic as standard equipment so why bother with a manual when the car can shift for you for no addition John Kissane Motorola Ireland ' ' UUCP motcid glas kissanej Mahon Industrial Estate Internet Blackrock Cork Ireland U Doug Zolmer Internet Disclaimer My opinions only Bell Northern Research Ottawa Ontario Canada Service Control Point Routing Services Design R